The following speeches were delivered in Parliament during the debate on the State of the Nation Address. Andrew Whitfield MP – Ramaphosa’s broken promises have real consequences DA Shadow Minister of Police Dennis Ryder MP- Thieving ANC the cause of municipal collapse DA NCOP Spokesperson for Finance and Appropriations  Baxolile Nodada MP – The ANCs broken education system is loadshedding the future of young South Africans DA Shadow Minister of Basic Education Mlindi Nhanha MP – Government failure is the norm under the ANC DA NCOP Spokesperson for Public Enterprises, Mineral Resources and Energy Nazley Sharif MP- Gender-Based Violence and Femicide victims still left behind by government DA Shadow Deputy Minister of Women, Youth and People with Disabilities